other_findings.model_claim: [Pool address is deterministic (cloneDeterministic salt = token0, token1, tickSpacing) and creation is permissionless. The first transaction to call createPool permanently sets the initial price via CLPool.initialize(_sqrtPriceX96). A mempool observer can front-run an intended pool creator and initialize the pool with an arbitrary price, causing the victim’s transaction to revert (pool already exists) and leaving a manipulated initial price that can economically harm early LPs/traders who trust expected initialization.]
